<h2 id="what-is-peek-pro">📋 What Is Peek Pro?</h2>

Peek Pro is a cloud-based booking and operations platform built specifically for tours, activities, attractions, and experience-based businesses. Founded in 2012, the platform has evolved from a simple booking widget into a comprehensive operations suite that handles reservations, waivers, point-of-sale, resource management, and multi-channel distribution.

Unlike horizontal booking tools that try to serve everyone from dentists to dog groomers, Peek Pro focuses exclusively on the experience economy. This specialization shows in features like manifest management, guide scheduling, equipment tracking, and integrations with OTAs like Viator, GetYourGuide, and Expedia.

The platform operates on two pricing models: a zero-subscription model where Peek takes a percentage of each booking plus payment processing, or a flat monthly fee for higher-volume operators. This flexibility makes it accessible to seasonal operators while remaining cost-effective for large-scale businesses processing thousands of bookings monthly.

<h2 id="our-experience">🔍 Our Experience Testing Peek Pro</h2>

Our team has evaluated Peek Pro across multiple operator contexts over the past four years. We've seen it deployed in kayak tour operations running 3 locations, zip line parks with 15+ activity types, and urban walking tour companies managing 50+ guides across multiple cities.

The implementation process varies dramatically based on operation complexity. A single-location surf school can be fully operational within a week. A multi-location adventure park with equipment dependencies, certification requirements, and complex pricing tiers? Expect 4-6 weeks of configuration and staff training.

What consistently impressed us: the platform handles complexity without collapsing. We watched one operator manage 127 different tour products across 8 locations from a single dashboard. The resource allocation engine prevented double-booking guides and equipment even when bookings came simultaneously from the website, phone sales, and three different OTA channels.

What consistently frustrated us: the learning curve is real. Staff members comfortable with simpler tools like Checkfront or Rezdy often needed 2-3 weeks before feeling confident with Peek Pro's interface. The depth of functionality creates cognitive load that smaller operations may not need.

We also tested the customer support extensively. Response times averaged 4 hours for standard tickets and under 30 minutes for urgent issues during business hours. The dedicated success manager program for larger accounts proved valuable—operators with assigned managers reported significantly smoother implementations and faster issue resolution.

<h2 id="key-features">⚡ Key Features That Matter for Operators</h2>

<h3>Unified Inventory & Resource Management</h3>

This is where Peek Pro separates from competitors. The platform treats your operation as an interconnected system, not just a calendar with time slots.

Define your resources—guides, vehicles, equipment, locations—and set capacity constraints. When a booking comes in, Peek Pro checks availability across all dependencies. If your sunset kayak tour requires 2 guides, 12 kayaks, and 12 life jackets, the system won't accept booking 13 even if your calendar looks open.

For operators running multiple activity types sharing resources, this prevents the nightmare scenario we've seen tank businesses: accidentally overbooking because your zip line tour and your rappelling tour both need the same safety equipment.

<h3>Dynamic Pricing Engine</h3>

Peek Pro's SmartPricing feature adjusts rates based on demand signals, time until departure, and current booking velocity. Set your floor and ceiling prices, define the rules, and let the algorithm optimize revenue.

We tracked one whale watching operator who implemented dynamic pricing and saw 18% revenue increase in the first season without adding capacity. The system raised prices on high-demand weekend morning slots while discounting slower midweek departures to fill empty seats.

<div class="callout-orange">
<strong>Warning:</strong> Dynamic pricing requires monitoring. We've seen operators set overly aggressive rules that priced themselves out of shoulder season bookings. Start conservative—you can always expand the price range after gathering data.
</div>

<h3>Multi-Channel Distribution</h3>

Connect to OTAs, reseller networks, and affiliate partners through Peek Pro's distribution hub. Inventory syncs in real-time, preventing overselling when bookings come from multiple sources.

The platform integrates directly with Viator, GetYourGuide, Expedia Local Expert, TripAdvisor, and dozens of regional distribution partners. Commission structures and rate parity rules can be managed per channel.

For operators serious about distribution, check our guide on <a href="/guides/ota-channel-management">OTA channel management strategies</a> to maximize these integrations.

<h3>Digital Waivers & Check-In</h3>

Built-in waiver functionality eliminates third-party waiver fees. Customers sign digitally during booking or at check-in via tablet kiosks. Waivers attach to customer profiles permanently, so returning guests don't re-sign.

The check-in flow supports QR code scanning, dramatically reducing lobby congestion. One adventure park we consulted reduced average check-in time from 8 minutes to 90 seconds after implementing Peek Pro's kiosk system.

<h3>Point-of-Sale Integration</h3>

PeekPay handles on-site transactions with integrated hardware. Sell add-ons, merchandise, and walk-up bookings from the same system managing your online reservations. Inventory tracks across channels, and reporting consolidates everything.

This matters more than operators realize initially. Running separate POS and booking systems creates reconciliation headaches, inventory discrepancies, and reporting blind spots. Unified systems save hours weekly at scale.

<h3>Reporting & Analytics</h3>

Dashboards cover booking trends, revenue by channel, guide performance, resource utilization, and customer acquisition sources. Export capabilities support custom analysis, and scheduled reports can auto-deliver to stakeholders.

The attribution tracking deserves mention—Peek Pro traces bookings back to marketing campaigns when properly configured with UTM parameters, helping operators understand true customer acquisition costs.

